International Privacy Policy
Last updated: July 08, 2024
Go to:
US Service Privacy Policy
US Website Privacy Policy
International Service Privacy Policy
US Service Privacy Policy
US Website Privacy Policy
International Service Privacy Policy
1.
INTRODUCTION
Seesaw, Inc’s (“
Seesaw
“, “
we
“, “
us
” or “
our
“) mission is to create an environment where students can be their best. Protecting your and your child(ren)’s privacy is fundamental to our mission and business. We operate a learning experience platform that brings together premium instructional tools and curriculum, inclusive two-way communication, deep learning insights and progress monitoring (the “
Seesaw Service
“).
This International Privacy Policy (this “
Privacy Policy
”) sets out how we collect, store, process, transfer, share and use data that identifies, can reasonably identify or is associated with you or, if a parent, your child(ren) (your “
Personal Information
”) when you access or use the Seesaw Service outside the United States.
The terms of this Privacy Policy are generally applicable to your access and use of the Seesaw Service. However, we indicate where parts of this policy apply ONLY if you access and use the Seesaw Service from Australia, the EEA, New Zealand, Canada, or the UK.
Please ensure that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy before accessing and using, or, if you are a parent, allowing your child(ren) to access or use the Seesaw Service. If you have any questions, comments or requests regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us using the details set out in the “How to contact us” section below.
2.
WHO IS RESPONSIBLE FOR YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION?
We work with schools to make the Seesaw Service available to school administrators, teachers, students (i.e. parent’s child(ren)) and parents. How we share responsibility for using your Personal Information between us and the school, or, where applicable, the local authority or education board responsible for managing suppliers and service providers for the school (the “school administration”) will vary depending on where the school or school administration is located.
Information for schools and users in the UK or EEA
“
Controller
” means the entity that determines how and why your Personal Information is collected and used.
“
Processor
” means the entity that processes your Personal Information at the instruction of the
controller
. The
controller
remains responsible for your Personal Information at all times.
Where we act as a “processor”
We mostly use Personal Information as a
processor
on behalf of the relevant school or school administration. This means that the school or school administration determines and is responsible for how we process Personal Information.
For further information about how we process Personal Information on behalf of schools and school administrations, you can view the descriptions in our
Data Processing Agreement
. However, if your school uses the Seesaw Service and has uploaded your Personal Information to the Seesaw Service, you should consult that school’s privacy notice for information about how that Personal Information is used.
If you sign up as a teacher to the Seesaw Service with a free account, you must make sure that you have the relevant school’s authorisation to do so. When you sign up with your school’s authorisation, we will process Personal Information uploaded to the Seesaw Service as a
processor
on behalf of your school; however, if you sign up independently or without the school’s authority you will be the
controller
of, and responsible for the processing of Personal Information relating to students and parents that you or they upload to the Seesaw Service. We will use such Personal Information as a
processor
on your behalf as set out in our
Data Processing Agreement
.
Where we act as a “controller”
We also may process some Personal Information as a
controller
as described in this Privacy Policy, meaning that we determine and are responsible for how your and, if you are a parent, your child(ren)’s Personal Information is used.
Where we act as “joint controllers”
For certain processing described in the section headed “
Information collected automatically about all users of the Seesaw Service”
, we act as a joint
controller
with the relevant school or school administration, meaning that we jointly determine and are responsible for how your Personal Information is used.
We and the school have allocated responsibility for complying with our obligations under applicable data protection law as follows:
Information about how we use your Personal Information
: we will provide you, on behalf of both us and the school, with information in this Privacy Policy about how your Personal Information is used by us as joint
controllers
.
Your rights
: we will serve as the primary contact point for exercising your rights in respect of the Personal Information we process as joint
controllers
(as further described in the “Your Privacy Rights” section below). If you would like to exercise your rights in respect of your Personal Information, you can do so by contacting us using the details in the “
How to contact us
” section below.
Security
: we will store and maintain safeguards to ensure that the Personal Information we process as joint
controllers
is kept secure.
Lawfulness
: we have determined the lawful basis relied on for processing your Personal Information as joint
controllers
, as set out in the section headed “
Information collected automatically about all users of the Seesaw Service
” below.
Transfers
: we have implemented safeguards for the transfers of your Personal Information we undertake, including transfers outside of the jurisdiction you are in, as set out in the “
International Transfers
” section below.
Information for schools and users in Canada, Australia and New Zealand
Apart from as expressly stated in this Privacy Policy (or as directed by your school administration), Seesaw does not access, collect, use or disclose any Personal Information of teachers, parents or the child(ren) of parents which, at all times, remains under the control of your school or school administration. Please refer to your school’s privacy policy as to how your information is collected, used and/or disclosed by your school administration.
Before allowing a student to use the Seesaw Service you, as a teacher or school administrator (as determined in accordance with your school’s policies) must obtain parental or guardian approval for that student (i.e. their child) to use the Seesaw Service. In doing so, you must provide a copy or a link to this Privacy Policy to the student’s parent/guardian and explain that Seesaw will collect, use and disclose their and their child(ren)’s Personal Information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
Without limiting the above, school administration, teachers and parents that upload any Personal Information into the Seesaw Service must obtain the approval of all third parties (other than a parent’s child(ren)) whose Personal Information is uploaded to or used in the Seesaw Service by you, including referring them to this Privacy Policy.
