Information for schools and users in Australia and New Zealand
The information contained in this section constitutes our notification to you of our collection, use and disclosure of your Personal Information in accordance with Australian Privacy Principle 5 and New Zealand’s Information Privacy Principle 3.
If you are in Australia, by using the Seesaw Service you (and, if a parent, on behalf of your child(ren)) consent to the Seesaw’s collection of any of your sensitive information (as defined in the Privacy Act 1988), including in the following information types listed in Section 6 of this Privacy Policy:
Content and posts uploaded to online classrooms by teachers
Activities designed using the Seesaw service hosted on the ‘Community Library’
Messages sent between teachers and students/your child(ren)through the Seesaw service
Activities assigned to the student/your child(ren) by their teacher and completed by the student including their responses
Content (images, text, audio) uploaded by the student as part of their journal on the Seesaw Service
Profile photo used on a teacher’s/student’s account
