We automatically collect certain Personal Information about how you access and use our website at
www.seesaw.me
(our “Website”), and information about the device you use to access and use the Website. We collect and process the following information in this way and, if you are in the EEA or UK, we do so as a controller,
and if you are in Canada we do so as an accountable organization
:
Information about the device you use to access the Website
, such as IP address, unique device identifying numbers, type of device used, operating system, screen size, browser type, browser window size and device model and your approximate location derived from your IP address.
How we use it
Lawful basis we rely on (EEA / UK)
We use information about how you use and connect to the Website to present the Website to you on your device.
The processing is necessary for our legitimate interests, namely to provide the Website to the user.
We use this information to monitor and detect fraud or suspicious activity on our Website.
The processing is necessary for our legitimate interests, namely monitoring fraud and suspicious activity on our Website.
We aggregate this information to monitor the performance of the Website, to identify errors and ways in which we can improve the Website, including developing new features of the Website.
We will only use your Personal Information in this way to the extent you have given us your consent to do so.
We use this information alongside our advertising partners, as described in the section headed “Online advertising” below to serve you targeted advertising on other websites that you visit, and to identify how effective those advertisements are.
We will only use your Personal Information in this way to the extent you have given us your consent to do so.
Information about how you interact with the Website
, such as the pages you view and features you use on the Website, and any errors that occur on our Website while you are using it.
How we use it
Lawful basis we rely on (EEA / UK)
We use information about how you use and connect to the Website to present the Website to you on your device.
The processing is necessary for our legitimate interests, namely to provide the Website to the user.
We use this information to monitor and detect fraud or suspicious activity on our Website.
The processing is necessary for our legitimate interests, namely monitoring fraud and suspicious activity on our Website.
We aggregate this information to monitor the performance of the Website, to identify errors and ways in which we can improve the Website, including developing new features of the Website.
